OL,3,CAlderney's top politician says review
OL,4,Cinto economic deal is 'sensible'
OL,6,FAlderney's leading politician says it
OL,7,Fis "sensible" for there to be a review
OL,8,Finto the island's post-war financial
OL,9,Fdeal with Guernsey.
OL,11,FBill Abel, Chair of the Policy and
OL,12,FFinance Committee, told ITV News that
OL,13,Freviewing the agreement is timely
OL,14,Fgiven the #24 million deficit faced by
OL,15,Fthe States of Guernsey.
OL,17,FThe current arrangement, put in place
OL,18,Fin 1948, states that Guernsey funds
OL,19,FAlderney's key services, in return for
OL,20,Fthe island's income tax revenue.
